#35: 
This patch adds functions necessary to find the IOMMU resources for a specific

WARNING:AVOID_BUG: Avoid crashing the kernel - try using WARN_ON & recovery code rather than BUG() or BUG_ON()
#96: FILE: arch/x86/kernel/amd_iommu.c:509:
+	BUG_ON(!dev || dev->bus != &pci_bus_type || !dev->dma_mask);

BUG() or BUG_ON() should be avoided totally.
Use WARN() and WARN_ON() instead, and handle the "impossible"
error condition as gracefully as possible.

See: https://www.kernel.org/doc/html/latest/process/deprecated.html#bug-and-bug-on

CHECK:COMPARISON_TO_NULL: Comparison to NULL could be written "!iommu"
#111: FILE: arch/x86/kernel/amd_iommu.c:524:
+	if (*iommu == NULL)

Comparisons to NULL in the form (foo == NULL) or (foo != NULL)
are better written as (!foo) and (foo).

CHECK:COMPARISON_TO_NULL: Comparison to NULL could be written "!domain"
#115: FILE: arch/x86/kernel/amd_iommu.c:528:
+	if (*domain == NULL) {

WARNING:PREFER_PR_LEVEL: Prefer [subsystem eg: netdev]_info([subsystem]dev, ... then dev_info(dev, ... then pr_info(...  to printk(KERN_INFO ...
#118: FILE: arch/x86/kernel/amd_iommu.c:531:
+		printk(KERN_INFO "AMD IOMMU: Using protection domain %d for "

WARNING:SPLIT_STRING: quoted string split across lines
#119: FILE: arch/x86/kernel/amd_iommu.c:532:
+		printk(KERN_INFO "AMD IOMMU: Using protection domain %d for "
+				"device ", (*domain)->id);

Quoted strings that appear as messages in userspace and can be
grepped, should not be split across multiple lines.

See: https://lore.kernel.org/lkml/20120203052727.GA15035@leaf/

